<heading id="832C92574334C91AFF1805D9D27EB8D5" bold="true" box="[140,835,165,192]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="1">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFF1805D9D27EB8D5" bold="true" box="[140,835,165,192]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB84334C91AFE3905D9D3B1B8D5" authority="Hope" authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" box="[429,652,165,192]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFE3905D9D304B8D5" bold="true" box="[429,569,165,192]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Philorhizus</emphasis>
Hope
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="A0CC65AB4334C91AFD4B05D9D27EB8D5" box="[735,835,165,192]" name="Greece" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Greece</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="90C176B04334C915FF180591D56EBA35" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="key">
<keyStep id="632F3D9E4334C91AFF180591D569BA9F" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF180591D569B9CF" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF180591D569B9CF" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
1 Pronotum very narrow (ratio width/length 1.21-.36), with posterior angles obtuse and angled strongly forward (at about the length of antennomere 2), and therefore its base laterally strongly rounded toward posterior angles. Tempora long, almost as long as eye diameter, or somewhat shorter, almost rectilinearly narrowed, distinctly set off against neck (see 
<figureCitation id="40E039BE4334C91AFCEB0406D2F8B981" box="[895,965,378,404]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[140,174,1654,1676]" captionTargetBox="[150,1102,1292,1624]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[140,1109,1284,1634]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Philorhizus marggii n. sp. male genitalia, median lobe, lateral view, holotype. Scale bar 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2652727/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="40E039BE4334C91AFC460406D2DCB981" box="[978,993,378,404]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[140,174,1090,1112]" captionTargetBox="[140,1108,430,1070]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[137,1111,165,1070]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitat of Philorhizus marggii n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2652729/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">3</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4334C91AFB9C0406D008B9AD" author="Wrase DW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="807 - 813" part="37" refId="ref3956" refString="Wrase DW (2005) Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini). Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (1): 807 - 813." title="Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini)" type="journal article" year="2005">Wrase, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Two species from the 
<collectingRegion id="1A1FEBD94334C91AFDD604E1D3F3B9A2" box="[578,718,413,439]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Peloponnese</collectingRegion>
(Aroania and Taygetos Mts., with strongly reduced hindwings, elytra with completely rounded humeri ......... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF180498D569BA9F" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF180498D569BA9F" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
– Pronotum wider (ratio width/length &lt;1.21), with posterior angles less obtuse and only weakly angled forward, its base weakly rounded laterally toward posterior angles (see 
<figureCitation id="40E039BE4334C91AFE720756D310BA51" box="[486,557,554,580]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[140,174,1654,1676]" captionTargetBox="[150,1102,1292,1624]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[140,1109,1284,1634]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Philorhizus marggii n. sp. male genitalia, median lobe, lateral view, holotype. Scale bar 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2652727/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 15, 16, 17 in 
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4334C91AFD750756D248BA51" author="Sciaky R" box="[737,885,554,580]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky, 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Tempora short, ± distinctly curved to the neck. Macropterus or micropterous species with a wider distribution ....................................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="632F3D9E4334C91AFF1807EFD56EBBD2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF1807EFD56EBB03" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF1807EFD56EBB03" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
2. Unicolorous pale yellowish red, only dorsal side of head and an indistinct macula in posterior half of elytra rusty red. Tempora almost as long as eye diameter. Alpine regions of northern mountains in 
<collectingRegion id="1A1FEBD94334C91AFCA307A6D2FEBAE1" box="[823,963,730,756]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Peloponnese</collectingRegion>
................... ................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB84334C91AFD700780D56EBB03" authority="(Meschnigg, 1934)" authorityName="Meschnigg" authorityYear="1934" baseAuthorityName="Meschnigg" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[740,1107,764,791]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpinus">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFD700780D56EBB03" bold="true" box="[740,1107,764,791]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFD700780D251BB02" bold="true" box="[740,876,764,791]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ph. alpinus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4334C91AFCEE0780D576BB03" author="Meschnigg J" box="[890,1099,764,790]" journalOrPublisher="Entomologischer Anzeiger" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="65 - 68" part="14" refId="ref3773" refString="Meschnigg J (1934) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Coleopteren vom Balkan. Entomologischer Anzeiger 14: 65 - 68." title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Coleopteren vom Balkan" type="journal article" year="1934">Meschnigg, 1934</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF18065DD56EBBD2" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF18065DD56EBBD2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
– Head (more or less dark reddish) piceous, elytra with a distinct, wide, dark transverse fascia at apical half extending forward along suture, omitting a large, testaceous semicircular or square area around sutural angle, abdomen dark. Tempora somewhat shorter. Alpine regions of Taygetos Mountains in 
<collectingRegion id="1A1FEBD94334C91AFF6206D1D0BFBBD2" box="[246,386,941,967]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Peloponnese</collectingRegion>
.................................................................. 
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFCF306D0D56EBBD2" bold="true" box="[871,1107,940,967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB84334C91AFCF306D0D2CFBBD2" authority="Wrase &amp; Assmann, 2008" authorityName="Wrase &amp; Assmann" authorityYear="2008" box="[871,1010,940,967]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marggii" status="nov. sp.">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFCF306D0D2CFBBD2" bold="true" box="[871,1010,940,967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ph. marggii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F19C44524334C91AFC6D06D1D56EBBD2" box="[1017,1107,941,967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">nov. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="632F3D9E4334C91AFF1806ACD569BC8F" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF1806ACD56EBC46" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF1806ACD56EBC46" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
3. Strongly brachypterous, elytra very short (ratio length/width 1.22-1.30), with completely rounded humeri. Elytral basal third testaceous. Small species (
<quantity id="1F2388DE4334C91AFBB1068FD068BC24" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="3.0999999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="2.8">2.8- 3.4 mm</quantity>
). Southern Greek mainland (Parnassos) and northern mountains in 
<collectingRegion id="1A1FEBD94334C91AFF620146D0BFBC41" box="[246,386,1082,1108]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Peloponnese</collectingRegion>
............................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB84334C91AFCAF0145D56EBC46" authority="Wrase, 2005" authorityName="Wrase" authorityYear="2005" box="[827,1107,1081,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lompei">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFCAF0145D56EBC46" bold="true" box="[827,1107,1081,1108]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFCAF0145D287BC41" bold="true" box="[827,954,1081,1108]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ph. lompei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4334C91AFC540146D56EBC46" author="Wrase DW" box="[960,1107,1081,1108]" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="807 - 813" part="37" refId="ref3956" refString="Wrase DW (2005) Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini). Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (1): 807 - 813." title="Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini)" type="journal article" year="2005">Wrase, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF180121D569BC8F" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF180121D569BC8F" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">– Macropterus or micropterous species, elytra long (ratio length/width&gt;1.40), in both cases elytral humeri distinctly developed......................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="632F3D9E4334C91AFF1801DFD569BD3D" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF1801DFD569BCF5" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF1801DFD569BCF5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
4. Large species (
<quantity id="1F2388DE4334C91AFE0201DFD31EBCAB" box="[406,547,1187,1214]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="4.2" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="3.7">3.7-4.7 mm</quantity>
). Macropterous, elytral humeri dark brown. From the 
<collectingRegion id="1A1FEBD94334C91AFEB501BAD0BEBCF5" box="[289,387,1222,1248]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Canaries</collectingRegion>
to the Near East................ 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB84334C91AFD2301BAD569BCF5" authority="(Dejean, 1825)" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[695,1108,1222,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrisignatus">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFD2301BAD569BCF5" bold="true" box="[695,1108,1222,1249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFD2301BAD2A5BCF4" bold="true" box="[695,920,1222,1249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ph. quadrisignatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4334C91AFC3301BAD576BCF5" author="Dejean PFMA" box="[935,1099,1222,1248]" journalOrPublisher="Crevot, Paris" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref3595" refString="Dejean PFMA (1825) Species general des Coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean, Tome premier. Crevot, Paris." title="Species general des Coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean, Tome premier" type="book" year="1825">Dejean, 1825</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF180196D569BD3D" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF180196D569BD3D" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
– Smaller species (
<quantity id="1F2388DE4334C91AFE390195D306BD11" box="[429,571,1257,1284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.5">2.5-3.5 mm</quantity>
). Macropterous to micropterous, elytral humeri always light .................................................................................................5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="632F3D9E4334C91AFF18004CD569BDC2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF18004CD569BD85" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF18004CD569BD85" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
5. Elytra pale yellowish, as a rule with darkened suture. From western Mediterranean area to 
<collectingCountry id="A0CC65AB4334C91AFE0F002FD327BD78" box="[411,538,1363,1389]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Asia Minor</collectingCountry>
and Caucasus....................................................... ........................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB84334C91AFD39000AD569BD85" authority="(Dejean, 1825)" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[685,1108,1398,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanocephalus">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFD39000AD569BD85" bold="true" box="[685,1108,1398,1425]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294334C91AFD39000AD2A5BD84" bold="true" box="[685,920,1398,1425]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ph. melanocephalus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4334C91AFC33000AD576BD85" author="Dejean PFMA" box="[935,1099,1398,1424]" journalOrPublisher="Crevot, Paris" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref3595" refString="Dejean PFMA (1825) Species general des Coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean, Tome premier. Crevot, Paris." title="Species general des Coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean, Tome premier" type="book" year="1825">Dejean, 1825</bibRefCitation>
