<paragraph id="D864253B4334C91AFF1800E6D569BDC2" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C91AFF1800E6D569BDC2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">– Elytra always with dark pattern: dark transverse fascia in middle or at least a wide band along parts of suture and posterior part of lateral margin ........... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="632F3D9E4334C915FF18009CD576BA35" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="D864253B4334C915FF18009CD56EB93F" blockId="7.[140,1108,237,1671]" lastBlockId="8.[140,1108,166,545]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="632A860E4334C915FF18009CD56EB93F" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
6. Elytra on average more slender (ratio length/width 1.51-1.57, 
<geoCoordinate id="BDEF43FC4334C91AFC7E00A2D578BDEE" box="[1002,1093,1502,1531]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" precision="555" value="-1.54">Ø 1.54</geoCoordinate>
), almost parallel-sided, with narrow transverse dark fascia, dark pattern more cross-like, the central square-like macula often without connection to the lateral longitudinal darkenings. Pronotum usually darkened in middle. Internal sac of median lobe of aedeagus with tubular, long-winding structure, apically darkened by longer and denser microspines. Median lobe with longer apex (see Fig. 
<quantity id="1F2388DE433BC915FDFD05B6D394B8F1" box="[617,681,202,228]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.588" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="22.0">22 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA433BC915FD2505B6D271B8F1" author="Sciaky R" box="[689,844,202,228]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky, 1991</bibRefCitation>
). From western Mediterranean area, 
<collectingCountry id="A0CC65AB433BC915FE3A0591D30BB912" box="[430,566,237,263]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Asia Minor</collectingCountry>
, Middle East to Middle Asia. On the Balkan Peninsula with 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB8433BC915FE3E046DD30DB93F" authorityName="crucifer (Lucas" authorityYear="1846" box="[426,560,272,299]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="crucifer" subSpecies="crucifer">
ssp. 
<emphasis id="EAAFF929433BC915FE48046CD30DB93F" box="[476,560,272,298]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">crucifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
................................ 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB8433BC915FC8A0473D56EB93F" authority="(Lucas, 1846)" authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1846" baseAuthorityName="Lucas" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[798,1107,271,298]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifer">
<emphasis id="EAAFF929433BC915FC8A0473D56EB93F" bold="true" box="[798,1107,271,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="EAAFF929433BC915FC8A0473D295B93F" bold="true" box="[798,936,271,298]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ph. crucifer</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA433BC915FC23046CD576B93F" author="Lucas H" box="[951,1099,272,298]" journalOrPublisher="Gouvernement National, Paris." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref3669" refString="Lucas H (1846) Exploration scientifique de l'Algerie pendant les annees 1840, 1841, 1842, publiee par ordre du Gouvernement et avec le concours d'une Commission Academique. Sciences Physiques. Zoologie II. Histoire Naturelle des animaux articules, Deuxieme Partie Insectes. Gouvernement National, Paris." title="Exploration scientifique de l'Algerie pendant les annees 1840, 1841, 1842, publiee par ordre du Gouvernement et avec le concours d'une Commission Academique. Sciences Physiques. Zoologie II. Histoire Naturelle des animaux articules, Deuxieme Partie Insectes" type="journal volume" year="1846">Lucas, 1846</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D864253B433BC915FF180448D56EBA35" blockId="8.[140,1108,166,545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead id="632A860E433BC915FF180448D56EBA35" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
– Elytra on average wider (ratio length/width 1.41-1.54, 
<geoCoordinate id="BDEF43FC433BC915FC27044ED52CB95B" box="[947,1041,306,334]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" precision="555" value="-1.46">Ø 1.46</geoCoordinate>
) and slightly widened apically, with very variable colour pattern, transverse dark fascia usually very wide, but sometimes not distinct, disappearing. Pronotum rusty red, often darkened on disc. Internal sac of median lobe of aedeagus with 2 subparallel fields of denticles. Apex of median lobe shorter and rounded (see Fig. 
<quantity id="1F2388DE433BC915FDF7049FD399B9E8" box="[611,676,483,509]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="21.0">21 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA433BC915FD3A049FD277B9E8" author="Sciaky R" box="[686,842,483,509]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky, 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Whole of Europe to Near East ...................................................... 
